{
  "answer": "The famous opening couplet (sher) from Mirza Ghalib's ghazal in *Diwan-E-Ghalib* likens the world to a children's playground or game (*bazeecha-e-atfaal*) unfolding as a mere spectacle before him.[^1]\n\n**Original (Urdu, Nastaliq script):**  \nبازیچۂ_اطفال ہے دنیا مرے آگے  \nہوتا ہے شب_و_روز تماشا مرے آگے[^2]\n\n**Transliteration (Roman Urdu):**  \nbaazeecha-e-atfaal hai duniya mere aage  \nhota hai shab-o-roz tamasha mere aage[^3]\n\n**Translation (English):**  \nThis world is but a children's game, a vast display,  \nWhere night and day a spectacle unfolds my way.[^1]\n\nThis is the matla (opening couplet) of ghazal #213.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/#p-3132be).\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/original/#p-cb8975).\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/transliteration/#p-6c6c39).\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/).",
